Modelling of the PL-decay data was performed in two steps, based on the expression for Id(t) in Eq. (1). As the first step, we modelled the data set associated with the polymer Super Yellow, because it showed sufficiently strong ET effects. From these fits to data, we determined a value for the nominal acceptor concentration Ca that applies to MAPbI3 and is therefore set to remain unchanged from here onwards. We further determined the associated Förster radius R0SY\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
